Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Victor George Fitzpatrick appeared by video.  Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask appeared by video for Victor George Fitzpatrick.  Attorney Grace M. Gall appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Case adjourned to branch 40.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Victor George Fitzpatrick in court, appear by video with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask, appear by video.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 40, Judge Shelton. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 40.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Victor George Fitzpatrick in court in person.  Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for preliminary hearing. OPD needs additional time to appoint an attorney. State requests this matter be set for a State V Lee hearing in the trial court; denied. Court finds good CAUSE to adjourn preliminary hearing.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed:  OSPD Appointment of Counsel Report.

Defendant Victor George Fitzpatrick not in court, defendant in custody.  Adam Joseph Best appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.
Case set for a prelimnary hearing. State witness present. SPD has not appointed counsel. State requests the matter be sent to the trial court for a State V. Lee hearing. Request is denied. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with Markell Hughes (co-actor); AC (12/19/1976); AMK (09/20/1967); RDH (11/21/1997); TLR (08/16/1963);
No Contact Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 1 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.  No driving without a valid license.

Defendant Victor George Fitzpatrick in court with attorney Helmi Hamad.  Defendant Victor George Fitzpatrick in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Victor George Fitzpatrick appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Shelton, Branch 40. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL. Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count(s) 4 and 6. Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4). This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 9, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
